						<div class="postbody">I like examples!<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; This code:<br />INC $4014<br />NOP<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Yields these cycles<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <br />read:&nbsp; &nbsp;'INC' opcode<br />read:&nbsp; &nbsp;#$14<br />read:&nbsp; &nbsp;#$40<br />read:&nbsp; &nbsp;$4014<br />write:&nbsp; $4014&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;- trigger<br />write:&nbsp; $4014&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;- DMA attempts to halt, can't because it's a write<br />read:&nbsp; &nbsp;'NOP' opcode&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;- DMA attempts to halt, success!&nbsp; This becomes a dummy read<br />&nbsp; -rd:&nbsp; 'NOP' opcode&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;- 'alignment' dummy read **ONLY IF** DMA unit is on a 'put' cycle<br />read:&nbsp; &nbsp;$xx00&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;- DMA starts here .. this is a DMA read<br />write:&nbsp; $2004&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;- DMA write<br />...<br /></div></div>

